'''Nedungolam''' ({{Lang-ml|നെടുങ്ങോലം}}) or '''Nedumgolam''' is the Northern border town of [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur municipality]] in the [[Kollam district]] of [[Kerala]] state, [[India]].  Nedungolam is very near to the world-famous-wetland in [[Kollam district]], [[Polachira]], which is a favorite destination for migratory birds.<ref name="India Social">[http://www.indiasocial.org/cgi/news.asp?id=2885&sel=4 India Social Website]</ref> A census conducted on 2003 reveals that over 26,000 birds belonging to 37 species are visiting or living in the [[Polachira]] wetlands.<ref name="The Hindu">[http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/2003/05/02/stories/2003050209670300.htm Hindu Online National Daily]</ref>

== Importance of Nedungolam ==

Nedungolam is a town with two major junctions - Hospital Junction and Post Office Junction.<ref>[https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Hospital+Junction+Bus+Stop,+Paravur+-+Chathanoor+Rd,+Nedungolam,+KL+691301,+India/Nedungolam,+Kerala,+India/@8.8320996,76.6757655,16z/data=!4m14!4m13!1m5!1m1!1s0x3b05e4f401fe91bf:0x4a9e402f595c35c0!2m2!1d76.682038!2d8.833589!1m5!1m1!1s0x3b05e4f528ce467b:0x6b3a27e83049e9d5!2m2!1d76.6845832!2d8.8363607!3e0?hl=en Nedungolam in Google Map]</ref> It is one of the important attractions of blessed estuary land, [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur]]. Most of the resorts in [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur]] are very near to Nedungolam. Beautiful beaches of Paravur are just 5&nbsp;km away from Nedungolam. Proximity to the world-famous Kerala wetland, [[Polachira]] is another blessing of Nedungolam. In addition to that, one of the heritage sites of Kerala, [[Pozhikkara]] is just 5&nbsp;km from Nedungolam.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Tu0imj39FwkC&pg=PA186&lpg=PA186&dq=paravoor+pozhikkara+population&source=bl&ots=AhX2v3eBEh&sig=mKGlpcXgRR4ax6pVIb4cJnojY7k&hl=en&sa=X&ei=NolfU5aeKsaQuATA3ICgDg&ved=0CFgQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=paravoor%20pozhikkara%20population&f=false Coastal Zone Management]</ref>
Rama Rao Memorial Govt. Taluk Hospital, [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur]] - The one and only Taluk Hospital in [[Chathannoor]] constituency is in Nedungolam. Paravur Sub-Registrar Office, Padmanabha Rao public library, B.R Hospital - another famous hospital in [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur]] etc. - are the other important institutions in Nedungolam. Many Hindu temples, Nedungolam Service Co-operative Bank, Nedungolam Post-office<ref>[http://www.indianpostcodes.com/post-codes/nedungolam-pin-codes-quilon-691334 Nedungolam Post office]</ref> and Nedungolam Govt. Higher Secondary School are also situated in the locality of Nedungolam. Resorts in Nedungolam area include:
* Aquasserenne Resort, Paravur
* Fragrant Nature Hotels & Resorts Pvt Ltd., Paravur<ref>[http://www.tripadvisor.in/ShowUserReviews-g784581-d602105-r137960911-Fragrant_Nature_Hotels_Resorts_Kollam-Kollam_Kerala.html Fragrant Nature Resort, Paravur - Tripadvisor.in]</ref>
* The Tranquil Palms Resort, Paravur

== How to reach ==

Nedungolam is located at the borders of [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur Municipality]] and is in [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur]]-[[Chathannoor]] road. Nedungolam is well connected with almost all the major towns. It is about 18&nbsp;km from [[Kollam|Kollam City]] and 3&nbsp;km from [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur town]]. Private and [[Kerala State Road Transport Corporation|KSRTC]] bus services connect Nedungolam with various towns in [[Kerala]]. [[Paravur Municipal Bus Stand]] is 4&nbsp;km away from Nedungolam.

[[Paravur Railway Station]] is the nearest important railway station to Nedungolam, which is 3&nbsp;km from Nedungolam. 14 pairs of trains connect [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur]] with various Indian cities like [[Kollam]], [[Trivandrum]], [[Kochi]], [[Calicut]], [[Palakkad]], [[Thrissur]], [[Bengaluru]], [[Chennai]], [[Mumbai]], [[Madurai]], [[Kanyakumari]], [[Mangalore]], [[Pune]], [[Salem, Tamil Nadu|Salem]], [[Coimbatore]], [[Trichy]] and [[Tirunelveli]] through Indian Railways.
 
There are no airports in [[Kollam district]]. The nearest airport is [[Trivandrum International Airport]], about {{convert|57|km}} away.<ref name="airport">[http://www.trivandrumairport.com Thiruvananthapuram International airport]</ref> Daily domestic flight services are available to major cities like [[Mumbai]], [[Chennai]], [[Delhi]], [[Bangalore]] and [[Kochi]]. International flight services connecting to [[Sharjah (emirate)|Sharjah]], [[Dubai]], [[Abu Dhabi]], [[Bahrain]], [[Kuwait]], [[Muscat, Oman|Muscat]], [[Male]], [[Doha]], [[Singapore]] and [[Colombo]] are available from here.

